# 🗄️ ReportMyCity — Database Structure Documentation

This document outlines the **MongoDB** database schema used by the ReportMyCity Official Portal. The database is hosted on a local MongoDB instance and managed via the [Database](file:///home/ismail/Desktop/antigraviti/reportmycity/config/database.php#13-85) singleton in PHP.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Overview

- **Database Name**: `reportmycity`
- **Engine**: MongoDB (NoSQL)
- **Primary Key**: `_id` (Auto-generated `ObjectId`)
- **Connection**: `mongodb://localhost:27017`

---

## 📂 Collections Summary

### 1. `admins`
Stores administrative accounts responsible for managing the portal, assigning officers, and reviewing complaints.

| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `name` | `string` | Full name of the administrator. |
| `email` | `string` | Unique email for login. |
| `password` | `string` | BCrypt hashed password. |
| `role` | `string` | Always set to `admin`. |
| `created_at` | `string` | ISO formatted timestamp (`Y-m-d H:i:s`). |

---

### 2. `users`
Stores citizen accounts for reporting civic issues and tracking their history.

| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `name` | `string` | Citizen's full name. |
| `email` | `string` | Unique email for login. |
| `phone` | `string` | Unique verified 10-digit mobile number. |
| `password` | `string` | BCrypt hashed password. |
| `role` | `string` | Always set to `user`. |
| `created_at` | `string` | ISO formatted timestamp. |

---

### 3. `officers`
Stores field officer accounts (the workforce) assigned by admins to resolve specific complaints.

| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `name` | `string` | Officer's full name. |
| `email` | `string` | Professional email. |
| `phone` | `string` | Mobile number for contact. |
| `password` | `string` | BCrypt hashed password. |
| `role` | `string` | Always set to `officer`. |
| `created_at` | `string` | ISO formatted timestamp. |

---

### 4. `complaints`
The core collection storing all civic reports, their tracking history, and cross-references.

| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `user_id` | `ObjectId/String` | Reference to the `users` collection. |
| `title` | `string` | Short title of the issue. |
| `category` | `string` | Category (e.g., Road Damage, Garbage, Water Leakage). |
| `description` | `string` | Detailed text description of the issue. |
| `location` | `string` | Descriptive location string (e.g., Crossway 21). |
| `image` | `string` | Relative path to user-uploaded photo. |
| `date` | `string` | User-reported date of incident. |
| `status` | `string` | `Pending`, `In Progress`, `Officer Completed`, `Resolved`. |
| `admin_reply` | `string` | Official feedback from the administrator. |
| `officer_notes` | `string` | Progress report or final resolution notes from the officer. |
| `officer_proof_image` | `string` | Photo evidence uploaded by officer after work is done. |
| `assigned_officer_id` | `String` | Reference to the `officers` collection. |
| `assigned_officer_name` | `string` | Mirroring officer name for easy retrieval. |
| `additional_user_ids` | `array` | List of `user_id`s who reported the same issue (merged). |
| `created_at` | `string` | ISO formatted timestamp. |

---

### 5. `notifications`
Stores system alerts for real-time dashboard updates across all roles.

| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `user_id` | `String` | Target recipient ID (optional for role-based alerts). |
| `role` | `string` | Target access level (`admin`, `officer`, or `user`). |
| `message` | `string` | Visible alert content. |
| `is_read` | `boolean` | Read/Unread status tracker. |
| `created_at` | `string` | ISO formatted timestamp. |

---

## <i class="la la-bolt"></i> Indexing Strategy (Recommended)

To ensure high performance as the platform scales, the following indexes are implemented or recommended:

- **Users/Officers**: Unique index on `email`.
- **Users**: Unique index on `phone`.
- **Complaints**: Compounded index on `status` and `created_at` for dashboard queries.
- **Complaints**: Geospatial or text index on `location` for duplicate detection.
- **Notifications**: Index on `user_id` and `is_read` for quick alert counts.
